Issue #45048 reports: Wrong example. Problem: This example from the documentation (https://nodejs.org/api/process.html#when-to-use-queuemicrotask-vs-processnexttick)
```js
import { nextTick } from 'node:process';
Promise.resolve().then(() => console.log(2));
queueMicrotask(() => console.log(3));
nextTick(() => console.log(1));
// Output:
// 1
// 2
// 3
```
doesn't work in Windows (node 16.13 and 18.11) and Ubuntu (node 18.11). Actual output is always
```console
2
3
1
```
This looks like a documentation bug, but any explanation for this behavior in the main module would be appreciated. Resolution evidence: Linked PR #45093: doc: fix process.nextTick() scheduling differences between module types. Resolution type: linked_pr. Maintainer context: jasnell (MEMBER): Yeah, looks like it was never tested when the mjs version was added. This is a known scheduling difference between cjs and mjs. The mjs example just needs to be updated to reflect the correct ordering. Interested in opening a PR?

jasnell (MEMBER): That would be helpful yes.

